      • ys

        public static int ys(int i,
                     int j,
                     int m)
        Turns a 3D ZY coordinate into a 2D Y perspective coordinate.
        Parameters:
        i - The 3D Z point
        j - The 3D Y point
        m - There are two different ys() methods within NFM2, this integer is used to unify them while providing a way to distinguish between them. 0 is for using Medium.cz (normal) 1 is for using 10 (only found in Medium)
        Returns:
        The 2D Y coordinate.
